name: Tenkaichi Bushi: Keru Naguuru
overview: Tenkaichi Bushi Keru Nagūru (天下一武士 ケルナグール lit. The Greatest Warrior on Earth - Kick and Punch?) is a fighting video game developed by Game Studio and published by Namco. It was released for the Famicom on July 21, 1989 only in Japan. It is one of the earliest versus fighting games with role-playing video game elements.
